- Create log directory
  . mkdir /var/log/burrito
  . sudo chown <user> /var/log/burrito


- Install MongoDB
  . go to the website and install it:
    http://www.mongodb.org/downloads
  . move bin files to /usr/local/bin
    . alternatively, you can put add the bin path to PATH
  
  . create the database directory
    . mkdir /var/log/MongoDB

  . go to System Preferences -> Accounts -> your account -> Login Items
  . add a script with the following command:
    #!/bin/bash
    mongod --fork --quiet --dbpath /var/log/burrito/MongoDB --logpath /var/log/burrito/MongoDB/mongodb.log --logappend
  . log out and log in


- Install PyMongo
  . go to the website and install it:
    http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pymongo/#downloads
  . you can also use easy_install:
    easy_install pymongo


- Install argparse (for python)
  . easy_install argparse